Nigeria’s Super Eagles winger Victor Moses has announced his intention to quit the National team after earning his first cap in 2012. The 27-year -old Chelsea winger Victor Moses confirmed his retirement on Instagram account. “I would like to announce that after much thought I have made the decision to retire from playing international football,” a statement from his Instagram account. Moses steps down after playing all three matches for Nigeria at World Cup 2018 in Russia, with the Super Eagles eliminated in the group stage. Moses ends his international career with 37 caps and 12 goals. He played in two World Cups, and also helped the Super Eagles lift the 2013 Africa Cup of Nations.  Anthony Nlebem 